Christopher G. Miller is president of The Piedmont Environmental Council, a 501(c)3 nonprofit working to protect the natural resources, rural economy, history and beauty of the Virginia Piedmont.
He is a founding member of both the Coalition for Smarter Growth and the Choose Clean Water Coalition, and serves on the boards of the Virginia League of Conservation Voters, the Virginia Conservation Network, the Chesapeake Conservation Partnership and the Journey Through Hallowed Ground Partnership.
This commentary first appeared in The Virginia Mercury.